SPORTS GUIDELINES AND CONSIDERATIONS FOR CORVALLIS SPECTATORS -- With many home games starting soon. We wanted to make sure everyone knows and understands the guidelines and considerations for spectators visiting our fields. Please note we have expectations set for Phase 1, Phase 2, and Phase 3. We are currently in Phase 2. These guidelines were created in accordance with the Governor's Mandate, Ravalli County Health Department, other Ravalli School Districts, as well as the Corvallis School Board.

post_text: Just a reminder!! If you are wanting your student(s) to learn remotely to start the school year be sure to “enroll” your students in remote learning ASAP. Paperwork was sent home on Friday to all primary school students and anyone that did not choose in-person learning on our survey to start the year 5-12. If you are signing up to go remote you need to fill out this survey: https://bit.ly/CSDremote AND sign the paperwork that was sent home. If you did not receive any paperwork it can be filled out at the Central Office. All paperwork is due by Aug 21. Thanks Blue Devil Families.

Corvallis School District #1
August 5 at 1:35 AM ·

The Corvallis School District is seeking an individual to serve on the Board of Trustees until the next regular school election held in May 2021. This is a nonpartisan position and interested candidates must be a qualified voter of the Corvallis School District. A letter of interest is due to the District Office by noon on August 24, 2020. Interviews will be held on August 26 at 5:30 p.m., Corvallis High School Library. Please contact the Central Office at 961-4211 for more information.

post_text: Last Day for best pricing and free shipping!
shared_text:
Corvallis Primary School
June 30 at 4:13 PM ·

Today is the last day to order your Edu-kit with best pricing and free shipping to the Primary School!

Corvallis Primary School offers the EduKit program as a convenient option for busy families to order school supplies for the 2020/2021 year. EduKits include the supplies approved by your school.

Your student's order will be in the classroom on the first day of school.

Extended ordering is available from July 01 - July 31 for a $20 additional fee and will be delivered to your home shortly before school begins.

Please order the kit that corresponds with your student's assigned teacher.

shared_text:
Corvallis Schools Foundation
June 8 at 4:52 PM ·

CONGRATULATIONS to Brock Hammill, Tracy Dickerson and Jeff Kaiser for winning the 2019 Corvallis Schools Foundation Innovative Proposal Award.
The CSF board selects one grant recipient for the school year as having the most innovative idea. Their High School STEM Sensor project grant provided the tools to take science, physics, and anatomy experiments from students observing the teacher to a student hands-on experience.
The winner of the CSF innovation award receives $250 above and beyond the amount of their grant to be used in their classroom.

post_text:
You Are Invited!

Our CHS 2020 Senior Virtual Awards Ceremony is TONIGHT Thursday, June 4 at 7pm via our HS You Tube Channel at https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCaoHw1fqAUT0IaFgSCUsEIQ to CELEBRATE Seniors who won awards and scholarships.

Due to COVID, many scholarships are still pending, so they will not be announced during this viewing. The “mostly” complete list will be handed out at graduation this Saturday.

Get ready to celebrate!

Grab some snacks, some noise makers, relax and enjoy the evening!

Please take pictures of you celebrating and share them with Doug McConnaha either by creating a link on your phone, email to dougm@corvallis.k12.mt.us, One Drive or Google.

The 2020 Virtual Awards Will Be Available At 7pm – not earlier!

post_text:
The results of the community facilities survey have been posted on our webpage along with helpful Frequently Asked Questions page. The results from this and other surveys are one of many inputs the board will use when considering the timing and cost of a facilities bond. As of now, no bond timeline, amount, or scope has been determined. With the recent events locally and nationally, the District is patiently and thoughtfully considering options moving forward. On behalf of CSD#1, thank you Corvallis Community for your patience and input in this important process.

https://corvallisschools.org/csd-facilities/

Tim Johnson, Superintendent

Two separate homes are located at 280 First Street and 1151 Eastside Hwy, Corvallis, MT. Included in sale is the home and all of the home’s contents currently owned by the School District, for sale by sealed bid.

The attached land will not be sold in this transaction. Interested parties may submit a bid to the School District Central Office starting on May 11, 2020. Photographs of the home are available on the Corvallis School District Facebook, the Corvallisschools.org homepage, and the Central Office (more will be added).
